The data cleaning function¶

In [2]:
def transform(data: pd.DataFrame, 
              inplace=False )-> pd.DataFrame | None:
    """ 
    This function cleans the data frame INPLACE or as a new dataframe.
    :param data: The data frame to clean
    :param inplace: Whether to transform the dataframe in place or as a new dataframe
    :return: The transformed data frame as a new dataframe or none and transform it inplace
    """
    # Make a copy of the dataframe
    df = data if inplace else data.copy()
    # Convert datetime colun from  object to date
    df['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(df.datetime)
    # Extract year, month, day, and hour
    df['year'] = df.datetime.dt.year
    df['month'] = df.datetime.dt.month
    df['day'] = df.datetime.dt.day
    df['hour'] = df.datetime.dt.hour
    # One-Hot Encoding for both weather and season'
    df['W1'] = (df.weather == 1).astype(int)
    df['W2'] = (df.weather == 2).astype(int)
    df['W3'] = (df.weather == 3).astype(int)
    df['W4'] = (df.weather == 4).astype(int)
    df['spring'] = (df.season == 1).astype(int)
    df['summer'] = (df.season == 2).astype(int)
    df['fall'] = (df.season == 3).astype(int)
    df['winter'] = (df.season == 4).astype(int)
    # Drop useless column
    df.drop(['casual', 'registered', 'datetime', 'season', 'weather', 'atemp'], axis=1, inplace=True)
    # Return the transformed data frame as a new data frame
    return None if inplace else df
